54
00:03:45,940 --> 00:03:47,120
I don't know.

55
00:03:50,010 --> 00:03:51,590
You shouldn't go on that date tomorrow.

56
00:03:52,050 --> 00:03:53,030
It's too risky.

57
00:03:56,420 --> 00:03:57,080
Let me think.

58
00:03:58,010 --> 00:03:58,680
Let me think.

59
00:04:32,940 --> 00:04:34,480
When you see that umbrella,

60
00:04:35,570 --> 00:04:36,280
when you learn

61
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:37,600
about all the terrible things I've done,

62
00:04:38,940 --> 00:04:40,870
will you still stay with me?

63
00:04:58,860 --> 00:05:00,240
Do you remember that time

64
00:05:00,260 --> 00:05:01,550
we ran laps together in high school?

65
00:05:04,410 --> 00:05:05,310
Yeah.

66
00:05:05,330 --> 00:05:06,510
You got beaten up by Chi Hao

67
00:05:06,620 --> 00:05:07,390
and were feeling down,

68
00:05:07,530 --> 00:05:08,870
so I dragged you out for a run.

69
00:05:09,210 --> 00:05:10,630
You even tripped and fell.

70
00:05:11,300 --> 00:05:12,190
Thinking back,

71
00:05:12,330 --> 00:05:13,390
I wasn't exactly kind.

72
00:05:15,380 --> 00:05:16,360
When I showered later,

73
00:05:16,410 --> 00:05:17,800
I looked at all the bruises on my body.

74
00:05:17,890 --> 00:05:18,680
I couldn't even tell

75
00:05:18,700 --> 00:05:19,550
which ones were from the fight

76
00:05:19,770 --> 00:05:20,680
and which were from the fall.

77
00:05:21,330 --> 00:05:22,240
But at least the pain

78
00:05:22,260 --> 00:05:23,630
helped numb everything else.

79
00:05:26,260 --> 00:05:27,550
Since then,

80
00:05:28,180 --> 00:05:29,750
whenever I feel down,

81
00:05:30,140 --> 00:05:31,310
I come here to run.

82
00:05:32,770 --> 00:05:33,870
Do you still run?

83
00:05:35,010 --> 00:05:35,720
Sometimes.

84
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:46,920
Then will you

85
00:05:46,940 --> 00:05:47,990
run with me one more time?

86
00:05:52,090 --> 00:05:52,550
Sure.

87
00:05:53,260 --> 00:05:53,800
Let's go.

88
00:05:55,500 --> 00:05:55,990
Come on.

89
00:06:35,300 --> 00:06:36,680
Hurry up, Chi Ye!

90
00:06:39,700 --> 00:06:40,720
I can't keep up.

91
00:06:41,090 --> 00:06:41,840
Come on!

92
00:06:43,060 --> 00:06:43,750
Faster!

93
00:06:43,860 --> 00:06:44,920
Don't give up!

94
00:06:45,860 --> 00:06:46,680
Come on!

95
00:06:52,300 --> 00:06:52,920
That day,

96
00:06:53,650 --> 00:06:54,720
watching you run ahead of me,

97
00:06:55,940 --> 00:06:57,920
I told myself that one day,

98
00:06:58,530 --> 00:07:00,190
I'd run beside you.

99
00:07:04,090 --> 00:07:04,950
Keep going!

100
00:07:06,090 --> 00:07:06,920
Don't give up,

101
00:07:06,970 --> 00:07:07,680
Chi Ye!

102
00:07:07,820 --> 00:07:08,360
Come on!

103
00:07:08,620 --> 00:07:09,510
Keep going!

104
00:07:12,620 --> 00:07:13,550
How are you holding up?

105
00:07:15,450 --> 00:07:16,310
Are you okay?

106
00:07:16,890 --> 00:07:17,750
I'm fine.

107
00:07:21,650 --> 00:07:23,280
I've always longed to be with you,

108
00:07:24,450 --> 00:07:25,680
but after all these years,

109
00:07:26,820 --> 00:07:27,750
you still remain

110
00:07:29,330 --> 00:07:30,990
someone out of my reach.

111
00:07:39,140 --> 00:07:39,800
Chi Ye,

112
00:07:47,570 --> 00:07:48,280
now it's your turn

113
00:07:48,300 --> 00:07:49,280
to go somewhere with me.

114
00:07:57,500 --> 00:08:03,060
[OUTPATIENT]

115
00:08:08,740 --> 00:08:09,680
The doctor said

116
00:08:11,410 --> 00:08:12,390
her chances

117
00:08:13,500 --> 00:08:15,190
of waking up are slim.

118
00:08:17,620 --> 00:08:19,280
She might stay like this forever.

119
00:08:25,890 --> 00:08:26,680
No, she won't.

120
00:08:27,740 --> 00:08:28,990
Aunt Rong will wake up.

121
00:08:36,530 --> 00:08:37,270
Chi Ye,

122
00:08:49,340 --> 00:08:50,750
I once had a friend

123
00:08:53,100 --> 00:08:53,910
who was sincere

124
00:08:54,620 --> 00:08:55,360
and kind.

125
00:08:57,010 --> 00:08:57,870
I thought we'd be

126
00:08:57,930 --> 00:08:59,080
friends for life.

127
00:09:01,580 --> 00:09:02,670
But then

128
00:09:05,140 --> 00:09:06,270
I realized everything about him

129
00:09:06,380 --> 00:09:07,670
came with an agenda.

130
00:09:11,980 --> 00:09:13,870
Worst of all,

131
00:09:15,260 --> 00:09:16,750
he hurt my family.

132
00:09:18,530 --> 00:09:20,120
He put my mother in this bed.

133
00:09:25,860 --> 00:09:27,120
And yet, I still remember

134
00:09:29,500 --> 00:09:30,630
how good he was to me.

135
00:09:33,410 --> 00:09:35,270
All those memories from our youth

136
00:09:37,140 --> 00:09:38,320
felt real too.

137
00:09:41,770 --> 00:09:42,510
So,

138
00:09:45,930 --> 00:09:47,270
I want to ask him,

139
00:09:49,980 --> 00:09:51,870
which version of him is real?

140
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:01,440
So you know everything.

141
00:10:05,980 --> 00:10:06,910
Stop,

142
00:10:09,580 --> 00:10:10,990
before it's too late.

143
00:10:14,930 --> 00:10:16,080
It's already too late.

144
00:10:23,290 --> 00:10:24,320
People who made mistakes

145
00:10:26,460 --> 00:10:27,840
must pay the price.

146
00:10:28,530 --> 00:10:30,200
And what about the innocent people caught in the crossfire?

147
00:10:31,170 --> 00:10:32,560
Why should they suffer?

148
00:10:53,100 --> 00:10:53,960
I'm sorry.

149
00:10:57,580 --> 00:10:58,440
I'm sorry.

150
00:11:09,620 --> 00:11:10,990
Let's call off the engagement.

151
00:11:35,220 --> 00:11:35,840
Fine.

152
00:11:46,140 --> 00:11:47,480
One last question.

153
00:11:50,380 --> 00:11:51,320
Was there

154
00:11:54,410 --> 00:11:55,870
ever a moment,

155
00:11:57,690 --> 00:11:59,480
even just for a second,

156
00:12:00,810 --> 00:12:02,030
when you truly had feelings for me?

157
00:12:06,620 --> 00:12:07,510
Never.

158
00:12:44,620 --> 00:12:46,120
I knew from the start

159
00:12:46,690 --> 00:12:47,990
that Chi Ye wouldn't let go that easily.

160
00:12:49,980 --> 00:12:51,360
I've been there myself.

161
00:12:54,930 --> 00:12:55,600
Hatred is

162
00:12:55,650 --> 00:12:56,990
like a fire.

163
00:12:58,260 --> 00:12:59,790
Once it starts, it burns out of control

164
00:13:00,140 --> 00:13:01,390
and drives you crazy.

165
00:13:03,170 --> 00:13:04,560
By the time you realize it,

166
00:13:05,980 --> 00:13:07,560
you're already lost in the abyss.

167
00:13:12,010 --> 00:13:14,360
Is spending your whole life on revenge

168
00:13:15,460 --> 00:13:16,390
really worth it?

169
00:13:20,650 --> 00:13:22,200
It took me a long time to understand

170
00:13:23,290 --> 00:13:24,440
that hatred can never

171
00:13:24,460 --> 00:13:25,360
end hatred.

172
00:13:26,770 --> 00:13:28,560
Only love and forgiveness can.

173
00:13:31,410 --> 00:13:32,240
Maybe, in some ways,

174
00:13:35,380 --> 00:13:36,670
I'm luckier than Chi Ye.

175
00:14:24,380 --> 00:14:26,080
Why are you doing this to me?

176
00:14:28,930 --> 00:14:29,600
Why?

177
00:14:40,860 --> 00:14:41,600
Why?

178
00:14:43,410 --> 00:14:44,630
Why?

179
00:14:59,340 --> 00:14:59,870
Hello?

180
00:15:00,460 --> 00:15:00,840
Hello,

181
00:15:00,860 --> 00:15:02,240
is this Mr. Chi?

182
00:15:02,740 --> 00:15:04,240
I'm calling from Mofei Bakery

183
00:15:04,260 --> 00:15:05,240
to confirm

184
00:15:05,380 --> 00:15:07,390
the design and size of your wedding cake.

185
00:15:12,140 --> 00:15:12,840
Hello?

186
00:15:15,980 --> 00:15:17,440
Chi Ye is the one for me.

187
00:15:18,530 --> 00:15:20,080
I want to give him a chance.

188
00:15:21,580 --> 00:15:23,320
[Groom: Chi Ye]
I want to give myself a chance too.

189
00:15:24,740 --> 00:15:25,360
Nuo,

190
00:15:26,260 --> 00:15:27,560
will you marry me?

191
00:15:29,690 --> 00:15:30,630
Yes, I will.

192
00:16:22,770 --> 00:16:23,720
Xu Nuo,

193
00:16:27,620 --> 00:16:28,910
if you never loved me,

194
00:16:34,580 --> 00:16:36,270
why did you give me hope?

195
00:16:41,050 --> 00:16:42,240
If you never loved me,

196
00:16:42,340 --> 00:16:44,150
why did you give me hope?

197
00:16:48,260 --> 00:16:49,910
Was it just to mock me?

198
00:16:54,580 --> 00:16:55,200
Fine.

199
00:16:58,770 --> 00:16:59,790
If that's how it is,

200
00:17:03,690 --> 00:17:05,430
then I'll take you all down with me.

201
00:17:24,140 --> 00:17:24,710
Hello?

202
00:17:28,890 --> 00:17:30,230
Pull the trigger

203
00:17:32,060 --> 00:17:33,040
